history.content:
As the title says, I'm trying to enroll in a CS grad course as an undergrad. The professor gave me an enrollment code, and so I:

1) clicked on "Add" under "Class Adjustment" in CalCentral

2) Typed in the course number in "Enrollment Shopping Cart" and found the course

3) typed in the code in the "Permission Nbr" text box for the course

4) tried to enroll and got this message:  "Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request."

Does someone know how to resolve this issue? Thanks so much in advance!
history.subject: error trying to get in grad class with enrollment code
